40static void
41gf100_fifo_uevent_init(struct nvkm_fifo *fifo)
42{
43 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->engine.subdev.device;
44 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002140, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
45}
46
47static void
48gf100_fifo_uevent_fini(struct nvkm_fifo *fifo)
49{
50 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->engine.subdev.device;
51 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002140, 0x80000000, 0x00000000);
52}

54void
55gf100_fifo_runlist_update(struct gf100_fifo *fifo)
56{
57 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan;
58 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
59 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
60 struct nvkm_memory *cur;
61 int nr = 0;
62
63 mutex_lock(&subdev->mutex);
64 cur = fifo->runlist.mem[fifo->runlist.active];
65 fifo->runlist.active = !fifo->runlist.active;
66
67 nvkm_kmap(cur);
68 list_for_each_entry(chan, &fifo->chan, head) {
69 nvkm_wo32(cur, (nr * 8) + 0, chan->base.chid);
70 nvkm_wo32(cur, (nr * 8) + 4, 0x00000004);
71 nr++;
72 }
73 nvkm_done(cur);
74
75 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002270, nvkm_memory_addr(cur) >> 12);
76 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002274, 0x01f00000 | nr);
77
78#ifdef __NetBSD__
79 /* XXX it is wrong to wait under mutex */
80 if (cold) {
81 uint count = 2000;
82 while (count-- > 0) {
83 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00227c) & 0x00100000))
84 break;
85 delay(1000);
86 }
87 if (count == 0)
88 nvkm_error(subdev, "runlist update timeout\n");
89 } else {
90 int ret;
91
92 spin_lock(&fifo->runlist.lock);
93 DRM_SPIN_TIMED_WAIT_NOINTR_UNTIL(ret, &fifo->runlist.wait,
94 &fifo->runlist.lock, msecs_to_jiffies(2000),
95 !(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00227c) & 0x00100000));
96 if (ret == 0)
97 nvkm_error(subdev, "runlist update timeout\n");
98 spin_unlock(&fifo->runlist.lock);
99 }
100#else
101 if (wait_event_timeout(fifo->runlist.wait,
102 !(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00227c) & 0x00100000),
103 msecs_to_jiffies(2000)) == 0)
104 nvkm_error(subdev, "runlist update timeout\n");
105#endif
106 mutex_unlock(&subdev->mutex);
107}

109static inline int
110gf100_fifo_engidx(struct gf100_fifo *fifo, u32 engn)
111{
112 switch (engn) {
113 case NVKM_ENGINE_GR : engn = 0; break;
114 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSVLD : engn = 1; break;
115 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSPPP : engn = 2; break;
116 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSPDEC: engn = 3; break;
117 case NVKM_ENGINE_CE0 : engn = 4; break;
118 case NVKM_ENGINE_CE1 : engn = 5; break;
119 default:
120 return -1;
121 }
122
123 return engn;
124}
125
126static inline struct nvkm_engine *
127gf100_fifo_engine(struct gf100_fifo *fifo, u32 engn)
128{
129 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
130
131 switch (engn) {
132 case 0: engn = NVKM_ENGINE_GR; break;
133 case 1: engn = NVKM_ENGINE_MSVLD; break;
134 case 2: engn = NVKM_ENGINE_MSPPP; break;
135 case 3: engn = NVKM_ENGINE_MSPDEC; break;
136 case 4: engn = NVKM_ENGINE_CE0; break;
137 case 5: engn = NVKM_ENGINE_CE1; break;
138 default:
139 return NULL;
140 }
141
142 return nvkm_device_engine(device, engn);
143}
144
145static void
146gf100_fifo_recover_work(struct work_struct *work)
147{
148 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = container_of(work, typeof(*fifo), fault);
149 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
150 struct nvkm_engine *engine;
151 unsigned long flags;
152 u32 engn, engm = 0;
153 u64 mask, todo;
154
155 spin_lock_irqsave(&fifo->base.lock, flags);
156 mask = fifo->mask;
157 fifo->mask = 0ULL;
158 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&fifo->base.lock, flags);
159
160 for (todo = mask;
161 todo && (engn = __ffs64(todo), 1);
162 todo &= ~(1 << engn))
163 engm |= 1 << gf100_fifo_engidx(fifo, engn);
164 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002630, engm, engm);
165
166 for (todo = mask;
167 todo && (engn = __ffs64(todo), 1);
168 todo &= ~(1 << engn)) {
169 if ((engine = nvkm_device_engine(device, engn))) {
170 nvkm_subdev_fini(&engine->subdev, false);
171 WARN_ON(nvkm_subdev_init(&engine->subdev));
172 }
173 }
174
175 gf100_fifo_runlist_update(fifo);
176 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00262c, engm);
177 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002630, engm, 0x00000000);
178}
179
180static void
181gf100_fifo_recover(struct gf100_fifo *fifo, struct nvkm_engine *engine,
182 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan)
183{
184 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
185 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
186 u32 chid = chan->base.chid;
187
188 nvkm_error(subdev, "%s engine fault on channel %d, recovering...\n",
189 nvkm_subdev_name[engine->subdev.index], chid);
190 assert_spin_locked(&fifo->base.lock);
191
192 nvkm_mask(device, 0x003004 + (chid * 0x08), 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
193 list_del_init(&chan->head);
194 chan->killed = true;
195
196 fifo->mask |= 1ULL << engine->subdev.index;
197 schedule_work(&fifo->fault);
198}

200static const struct nvkm_enum
201gf100_fifo_sched_reason[] = {
202 { 0x0a, "CTXSW_TIMEOUT" },
203 {}
204};
205
206static void
207gf100_fifo_intr_sched_ctxsw(struct gf100_fifo *fifo)
208{
209 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
210 struct nvkm_engine *engine;
211 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan;
212 unsigned long flags;
213 u32 engn;
214
215 spin_lock_irqsave(&fifo->base.lock, flags);
216 for (engn = 0; engn < 6; engn++) {
217 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002640 + (engn * 0x04));
218 u32 busy = (stat & 0x80000000);
219 u32 save = (stat & 0x00100000); /* maybe? */
220 u32 unk0 = (stat & 0x00040000);
221 u32 unk1 = (stat & 0x00001000);
222 u32 chid = (stat & 0x0000007f);
223 (void)save;
224
225 if (busy && unk0 && unk1) {
226 list_for_each_entry(chan, &fifo->chan, head) {
227 if (chan->base.chid == chid) {
228 engine = gf100_fifo_engine(fifo, engn);
229 if (!engine)
230 break;
231 gf100_fifo_recover(fifo, engine, chan);
232 break;
233 }
234 }
235 }
236 }
237 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&fifo->base.lock, flags);
238}
239
240static void
241gf100_fifo_intr_sched(struct gf100_fifo *fifo)
242{
243 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
244 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
245 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00254c);
246 u32 code = intr & 0x000000ff;
247 const struct nvkm_enum *en;
248
249 en = nvkm_enum_find(gf100_fifo_sched_reason, code);
250
251 nvkm_error(subdev, "SCHED_ERROR %02x [%s]\n", code, en ? en->name : "");
252
253 switch (code) {
254 case 0x0a:
255 gf100_fifo_intr_sched_ctxsw(fifo);
256 break;
257 default:
258 break;
259 }
260}

321static void
322gf100_fifo_intr_fault(struct gf100_fifo *fifo, int unit)
323{
324 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
325 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
326 u32 inst = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002800 + (unit * 0x10));
327 u32 valo = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002804 + (unit * 0x10));
328 u32 vahi = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002808 + (unit * 0x10));
329 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00280c + (unit * 0x10));
330 u32 gpc = (stat & 0x1f000000) >> 24;
331 u32 client = (stat & 0x00001f00) >> 8;
332 u32 write = (stat & 0x00000080);
333 u32 hub = (stat & 0x00000040);
334 u32 reason = (stat & 0x0000000f);
335 const struct nvkm_enum *er, *eu, *ec;
336 struct nvkm_engine *engine = NULL;
337 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan;
338 unsigned long flags;
339 char gpcid[8] = "";
340
341 er = nvkm_enum_find(gf100_fifo_fault_reason, reason);
342 eu = nvkm_enum_find(gf100_fifo_fault_engine, unit);
343 if (hub) {
344 ec = nvkm_enum_find(gf100_fifo_fault_hubclient, client);
345 } else {
346 ec = nvkm_enum_find(gf100_fifo_fault_gpcclient, client);
347 snprintf(gpcid, sizeof(gpcid), "GPC%d/", gpc);
348 }
349
350 if (eu) {
351 switch (eu->data2) {
352 case NVKM_SUBDEV_BAR:
353 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001704, 0x00000000, 0x00000000);
354 break;
355 case NVKM_SUBDEV_INSTMEM:
356 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001714, 0x00000000, 0x00000000);
357 break;
358 case NVKM_ENGINE_IFB:
359 nvkm_mask(device, 0x001718, 0x00000000, 0x00000000);
360 break;
361 default:
362 engine = nvkm_device_engine(device, eu->data2);
363 break;
364 }
365 }
366
367 chan = nvkm_fifo_chan_inst(&fifo->base, (u64)inst << 12, &flags);
368
369 nvkm_error(subdev,
370 "%s fault at %010"PRIx64" engine %02x [%s] client %02x [%s%s] "
371 "reason %02x [%s] on channel %d [%010"PRIx64" %s]\n",
372 write ? "write" : "read", (u64)vahi << 32 | valo,
373 unit, eu ? eu->name : "", client, gpcid, ec ? ec->name : "",
374 reason, er ? er->name : "", chan ? chan->chid : -1,
375 (u64)inst << 12,
376 chan ? chan->object.client->name : "unknown");
377
378 if (engine && chan)
379 gf100_fifo_recover(fifo, engine, (void *)chan);
380 nvkm_fifo_chan_put(&fifo->base, flags, &chan);
381}
382
383static const struct nvkm_bitfield
384gf100_fifo_pbdma_intr[] = {
385/* { 0x00008000, "" } seen with null ib push */
386 { 0x00200000, "ILLEGAL_MTHD" },
387 { 0x00800000, "EMPTY_SUBC" },
388 {}
389};
390
391static void
392gf100_fifo_intr_pbdma(struct gf100_fifo *fifo, int unit)
393{
394 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
395 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
396 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x040108 + (unit * 0x2000));
397 u32 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x0400c0 + (unit * 0x2000));
398 u32 data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x0400c4 + (unit * 0x2000));
399 u32 chid = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x040120 + (unit * 0x2000)) & 0x7f;
400 u32 subc = (addr & 0x00070000) >> 16;
401 u32 mthd = (addr & 0x00003ffc);
402 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan;
403 unsigned long flags;
404 u32 show= stat;
405 char msg[128];
406
407 if (stat & 0x00800000) {
408 if (device->sw) {
409 if (nvkm_sw_mthd(device->sw, chid, subc, mthd, data))
410 show &= ~0x00800000;
411 }
412 }
413
414 if (show) {
415 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg), gf100_fifo_pbdma_intr, show);
416 chan = nvkm_fifo_chan_chid(&fifo->base, chid, &flags);
417 nvkm_error(subdev, "PBDMA%d: %08x [%s] ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s] "
418 "subc %d mthd %04x data %08x\n",
419 unit, show, msg, chid, chan ? chan->inst->addr : 0,
420 chan ? chan->object.client->name : "unknown",
421 subc, mthd, data);
422 nvkm_fifo_chan_put(&fifo->base, flags, &chan);
423 }
424
425 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x0400c0 + (unit * 0x2000), 0x80600008);
426 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x040108 + (unit * 0x2000), stat);
427}
428
429static void
430gf100_fifo_intr_runlist(struct gf100_fifo *fifo)
431{
432 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
433 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
434 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002a00);
435
436 if (intr & 0x10000000) {
437#ifdef __NetBSD__
438 spin_lock(&fifo->runlist.lock);
439 DRM_SPIN_WAKEUP_ONE(&fifo->runlist.wait, &fifo->runlist.lock);
440 spin_unlock(&fifo->runlist.lock);
441#else
442 wake_up(&fifo->runlist.wait);
443#endif
444 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002a00, 0x10000000);
445 intr &= ~0x10000000;
446 }
447
448 if (intr) {
449 nvkm_error(subdev, "RUNLIST %08x\n", intr);
450 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002a00, intr);
451 }
452}
453
454static void
455gf100_fifo_intr_engine_unit(struct gf100_fifo *fifo, int engn)
456{
457 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
458 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
459 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x0025a8 + (engn * 0x04));
460 u32 inte = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002628);
461 u32 unkn;
462
463 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x0025a8 + (engn * 0x04), intr);
464
465 for (unkn = 0; unkn < 8; unkn++) {
466 u32 ints = (intr >> (unkn * 0x04)) & inte;
467 if (ints & 0x1) {
468 nvkm_fifo_uevent(&fifo->base);
469 ints &= ~1;
470 }
471 if (ints) {
472 nvkm_error(subdev, "ENGINE %d %d %01x",
473 engn, unkn, ints);
474 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002628, ints, 0);
475 }
476 }
477}
478
479void
480gf100_fifo_intr_engine(struct gf100_fifo *fifo)
481{
482 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
483 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x0025a4);
484 while (mask) {
485 u32 unit = __ffs(mask);
486 gf100_fifo_intr_engine_unit(fifo, unit);
487 mask &= ~(1 << unit);
488 }
489}
490
491static void
492gf100_fifo_intr(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
493{
494 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = gf100_fifo(base);
495 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
496 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
497 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002140);
498 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002100) & mask;
499
500 if (stat & 0x00000001) {
501 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00252c);
502 nvkm_warn(subdev, "INTR 00000001: %08x\n", intr);
503 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x00000001);
504 stat &= ~0x00000001;
505 }
506
507 if (stat & 0x00000100) {
508 gf100_fifo_intr_sched(fifo);
509 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x00000100);
510 stat &= ~0x00000100;
511 }
512
513 if (stat & 0x00010000) {
514 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00256c);
515 nvkm_warn(subdev, "INTR 00010000: %08x\n", intr);
516 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x00010000);
517 stat &= ~0x00010000;
518 }
519
520 if (stat & 0x01000000) {
521 u32 intr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00258c);
522 nvkm_warn(subdev, "INTR 01000000: %08x\n", intr);
523 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0x01000000);
524 stat &= ~0x01000000;
525 }
526
527 if (stat & 0x10000000) {
528 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x00259c);
529 while (mask) {
530 u32 unit = __ffs(mask);
531 gf100_fifo_intr_fault(fifo, unit);
532 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00259c, (1 << unit));
533 mask &= ~(1 << unit);
534 }
535 stat &= ~0x10000000;
536 }
537
538 if (stat & 0x20000000) {
539 u32 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x0025a0);
540 while (mask) {
541 u32 unit = __ffs(mask);
542 gf100_fifo_intr_pbdma(fifo, unit);
543 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x0025a0, (1 << unit));
544 mask &= ~(1 << unit);
545 }
546 stat &= ~0x20000000;
547 }
548
549 if (stat & 0x40000000) {
550 gf100_fifo_intr_runlist(fifo);
551 stat &= ~0x40000000;
552 }
553
554 if (stat & 0x80000000) {
555 gf100_fifo_intr_engine(fifo);
556 stat &= ~0x80000000;
557 }
558
559 if (stat) {
560 nvkm_error(subdev, "INTR %08x\n", stat);
561 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002140, stat, 0x00000000);
562 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, stat);
563 }
564}
565
566static int
567gf100_fifo_oneinit(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
568{
569 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = gf100_fifo(base);
570 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
571 int ret;
572
573 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x1000, 0x1000,
574 false, &fifo->runlist.mem[0]);
575 if (ret)
576 return ret;
577
578 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x1000, 0x1000,
579 false, &fifo->runlist.mem[1]);
580 if (ret)
581 return ret;
582
583#ifdef __NetBSD__
584 spin_lock_init(&fifo->runlist.lock);
585 DRM_INIT_WAITQUEUE(&fifo->runlist.wait, "gf100fifo");
586#else
587 init_waitqueue_head(&fifo->runlist.wait);
588#endif
589
590 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 128 * 0x1000,
591 0x1000, false, &fifo->user.mem);
592 if (ret)
593 return ret;
594
595 ret = nvkm_bar_umap(device->bar, 128 * 0x1000, 12, &fifo->user.bar);
596 if (ret)
597 return ret;
598
599 nvkm_memory_map(fifo->user.mem, &fifo->user.bar, 0);
600 return 0;
601}
602
603static void
604gf100_fifo_fini(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
605{
606 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = gf100_fifo(base);
607 flush_work(&fifo->fault);
608}
609
610static void
611gf100_fifo_init(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
612{
613 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = gf100_fifo(base);
614 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
615 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
616 int i;
617
618 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000204, 0xffffffff);
619 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002204, 0xffffffff);
620
621 fifo->spoon_nr = hweight32(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002204));
622 nvkm_debug(subdev, "%d PBDMA unit(s)\n", fifo->spoon_nr);
623
624 /* assign engines to PBDMAs */
625 if (fifo->spoon_nr >= 3) {
626 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002208, ~(1 << 0)); /* PGRAPH */
627 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00220c, ~(1 << 1)); /* PVP */
628 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002210, ~(1 << 1)); /* PMSPP */
629 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002214, ~(1 << 1)); /* PMSVLD */
630 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002218, ~(1 << 2)); /* PCE0 */
631 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x00221c, ~(1 << 1)); /* PCE1 */
632 }
633
634 /* PBDMA[n] */
635 for (i = 0; i < fifo->spoon_nr; i++) {
636 nvkm_mask(device, 0x04013c + (i * 0x2000), 0x10000100, 0x00000000);
637 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x040108 + (i * 0x2000), 0xffffffff); /* INTR */
638 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x04010c + (i * 0x2000), 0xfffffeff); /* INTREN */
639 }
640
641 nvkm_mask(device, 0x002200, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
642 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002254, 0x10000000 | fifo->user.bar.offset >> 12);
643
644 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002100, 0xffffffff);
645 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002140, 0x7fffffff);
646 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002628, 0x00000001); /* ENGINE_INTR_EN */
647}
648
649static void *
650gf100_fifo_dtor(struct nvkm_fifo *base)
651{
652 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = gf100_fifo(base);
653 nvkm_vm_put(&fifo->user.bar);
654 nvkm_memory_del(&fifo->user.mem);
655 nvkm_memory_del(&fifo->runlist.mem[0]);
656 nvkm_memory_del(&fifo->runlist.mem[1]);
657#ifdef __NetBSD__
658 DRM_DESTROY_WAITQUEUE(&fifo->runlist.wait);
659 spin_lock_destroy(&fifo->runlist.lock);
660#endif
661 return fifo;
662}
663
664static const struct nvkm_fifo_func
665gf100_fifo = {
666 .dtor = gf100_fifo_dtor,
667 .oneinit = gf100_fifo_oneinit,
668 .init = gf100_fifo_init,
669 .fini = gf100_fifo_fini,
670 .intr = gf100_fifo_intr,
671 .uevent_init = gf100_fifo_uevent_init,
672 .uevent_fini = gf100_fifo_uevent_fini,
673 .chan = {
674 &gf100_fifo_gpfifo_oclass,
675 NULL
676 },
677};
678
679int
680gf100_fifo_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_fifo **pfifo)
681{
682 struct gf100_fifo *fifo;
683
684 if (!(fifo = kzalloc(sizeof(*fifo), GFP_KERNEL)))
685 return -ENOMEM;
686 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&fifo->chan);
687 INIT_WORK(&fifo->fault, gf100_fifo_recover_work);
688 *pfifo = &fifo->base;
689
690 return nvkm_fifo_ctor(&gf100_fifo, device, index, 128, &fifo->base);
691}
